trans-unit.source: Scheduler jobs may need to call out to services that require authentication.
trans-unit.target: Scheduler jobs may need to call out to services that require authentication.

trans-unit.source: This way, a called service can determine if the Scheduler job can access its resources.
trans-unit.target: This way, a called service can determine if the Scheduler job can access its resources.

trans-unit.source: Some of these services include other Azure services, Salesforce.com, Facebook, and secure custom websites.
trans-unit.target: Some of these services include other Azure services, Salesforce.com, Facebook, and secure custom websites.

trans-unit.source: Adding authentication to a Scheduler job is simple – add a JSON child element `authentication` to the `request` element when creating or updating a job.
trans-unit.target: Adding authentication to a Scheduler job is simple – add a JSON child element `authentication` to the `request` element when creating or updating a job.

trans-unit.source: Secrets passed to the Scheduler service in a PUT, PATCH, or POST request – as part of the `authentication` object – are never returned in responses.
trans-unit.target: Secrets passed to the Scheduler service in a PUT, PATCH, or POST request – as part of the `authentication` object – are never returned in responses.

trans-unit.source: In responses, secret information is set to null or may have a public token that represents the authenticated entity.
trans-unit.target: In responses, secret information is set to null or may have a public token that represents the authenticated entity.

trans-unit.source: To remove authentication, PUT or PATCH the job explicitly, setting the `authentication` object to null.
trans-unit.target: To remove authentication, PUT or PATCH the job explicitly, setting the `authentication` object to null.

trans-unit.source: You will not see any authentication properties back in response.
trans-unit.target: You will not see any authentication properties back in response.
